   "source": [
    "### 2.5 Encoding Categorical Variables\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- transform categorical features into a format that models can understand  \n",
    "- avoid incorrect numerical relationships between categories  \n",
    "- ensure the dataset is fully numerical before model training  \n",
    "\n",
    "**Observations:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- The dataset contained one categorical feature: **Status**  \n",
    "- Although **Sensor Position Side** was stored as a numerical value, it represents a categorical sensor location. \n",
    "  - so it was converted to a categorical type and encoded using dummy variables to avoid treating it as a continuous numerical feature\n",
    "- After standardisation, the Status column had two categories:\n",
    "  - **superheated**\n",
    "  - **subcooled**\n",
    "- One-hot (dummy) encoding was applied to convert this categorical feature into a numerical format  \n",
    "- A binary variable **Status_superheated** was created in which:\n",
    "  - 1 represents *superheated*  \n",
    "  - 0 represents *subcooled*  \n",
    "\n",
    "- The parameter `drop_first=True` was used to:\n",
    "  - avoid redundancy  \n",
    "  - prevent multicollinearity in linear models  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "969b401f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Identify categorical columns\n",
    "cat_cols = train_df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns.tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Sensor Position Side is stored as a number but represents categories\n",
    "# Convert it to categorical so it can be encoded properly\n",
    "train_df['Sensor Position Side'] = train_df['Sensor Position Side'].astype('category')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add Sensor Position Side to categorical columns\n",
    "cat_cols.append('Sensor Position Side')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Apply dummy encoding\n",
    "train_df = pd.get_dummies(\n",
    "    train_df,\n",
    "    columns=cat_cols,\n",
    "    drop_first=True,\n",
    "    dtype='int8'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convert boolean dummy column to integer\n",
    "train_df['Status_superheated'] = train_df['Status_superheated'].astype(int)"
   ]
