   "id": "ee6370eb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3.2 Defining feature & Target\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- define predictors and the output variable  \n",
    "- ensure the model learns the relationship between features and the target  \n",
    "\n",
    "**Observations:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- The target variable identified is **Target Pressure (bar)** \n",
    "- X contains all predictors, y contains the value to be predicted"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "id": "e63e3534",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Separate input features (X) and target variable (y)\n",
    "\n",
    "X = train_df.drop('Target Pressure (bar)', axis=1)\n",
    "y = train_df['Target Pressure (bar)']"
   ]
