  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c3384de1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 3.4 Feature Selection using Correlation Analysis and Random Forest Importance\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- examine the relationship between features and the target variable using correlation analysis\n",
    "- identify the most useful predictors for modelling\n",
    "- remove non-predictive variables such as Sensor ID\n",
    "- use Random Forest feature importance to capture non-linear relationships between features and target pressure\n",
    "- reduce noise and improve model interpretability before model training\n",
    "- performed using training data to avoid data leakage and ensure unbiased model evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "**Observations:**\n",
    "\n",
    "*Correlation Analysis:*\n",
    "- showed that only a few features have moderate linear relationships with the target variable where most features show weak correlation\n",
    "- For example:\n",
    "    - **Sensor Position Side_2** has a correlation of 0.486 which is the strongest positively correlated feature\n",
    "- These values indicate only **weak to moderate linear relationships** which suggests that the dataset is not strongly linearly dependent on individual features.\n",
    "\n",
    "*Random Forest feature importance:* \n",
    "- shows a strong **non-linear relationships**\n",
    "\n",
    "- The most important features identified were:\n",
    "    - Sensor Position Side_2= 0.237 (highest importance)\n",
    "    - Vapour Height (m)\t= 0.136\n",
    "    - Tank Length (m)\t= 0.111\n",
    "    - Sensor Position z\t= 0.103\n",
    "    - Sensor Position x\t= 0.071\n",
    "    - Sensor Position y\t= 0.065\n",
    "\n",
    "    - This clearly shows that **sensor position variables are highly influencing features**.\n",
    "\n",
    "- Features (with low importance < 0.01) that contribute little to prediction and may introduce noise were removed:\n",
    "    - Liquid Critical Temperature (K)= 0.0005\n",
    "    - Liquid Boiling Temperature (K)= 0.0011\n",
    "    - Status_superheated= 0.0007\n",
    "\n",
    "After applying the importance threshold of 0.01, the dataset has:\n",
    "- 17 input features\n",
    "- 1 target variable"
   ]
  },
