    "### 3.5 Target Variable Distribution Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- identify whether the target variable is **normally distributed or skewed**\n",
    "- detect **outliers**\n",
    "- determine if any **data transformation is required**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Observations:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- The histogram shows that the data is **highly right-skewed** in which most values concentrated between **0 and 0.5 bar**\n",
    "- The skewness value = **5.11** which indicates **extreme positive skewness**\n",
    "    - This shows that distribution is not normal and is heavily influenced by higher values\n",
    "- **mean (0.361)** > **median (0.203)** which also proves the presence of right skewness\n",
    "- **standard deviation (0.504)** > **mean (0.361)** which tells **significant variability** in the data\n",
    "- The boxplot confirms the presence of **a large number of outliers** particularly at higher pressure values\n",
    "\n",
    "This means that:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Models may **struggle to accurately predict extreme values**\n",
    "- Outliers may **increase prediction error**"
   ]
  },
