   "source": [
    "### 3.6 Feature Scaling\n",
    "\n",
    "**Purpose:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- to standardise continuous numerical variables so that differences in magnitude do not bias the learning process\n",
    "- without scaling, features with larger values could bias the learning process \n",
    "- improve model stability and performance\n",
    "- only continuous numerical features were scaled and binary (0/1) encoded variables were excluded to preserve their categorical meaning\n",
    "- each selected numerical feature is transformed to have a mean of zero and a standard deviation of one.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Observations:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- scaler was fitted only on the training dataset and then applied to the validation dataset to ensure no data leakage\n",
    "- Continuous variables (e.g. Vapour Height (m) and Tank Length (m)) were standardised\n",
    "- binary variables (Sensor Position Side and superheated)remained unchanged after scaling to preserving interpretability"
   ]
  },
